LOL, I may have embellished a little bit, but by less than you'd think. It's used as powerful decongestant, but does have some minor cognitive side effects that are similar to a low dose of Adderall (think on par with, like, 2.5-5mg worth). Just know that while the cognative effects are similar, albeit reduced, the effects on the rest of your body are pretty much full strength. Know, also, you're taking a shit-load more of it than you would Adderall. Think 120mg in a 12hr or 240mg in a 24, so don't think you can stack 'em to get the full effect of legit ADD meds (which come in 10-40mg). It's a good way to end up in the ER with heart palpitations. Still, if you've got attention issues and aren't treating them, an (extremely occasional) contraindicated use won't do you much harm. ...Just (slowly) throw coffee in the tank as well, to taste, to make up the difference in cognitive effect.

Sudafed (the actual one, not the Phenylephrine crap) is a drug from the amphetamine family. It's got a longer carbon chain off the Benzene ring than regular ol' amphetamine salts (It's actually an closer to Meth - go figure... There's an extra hydroxyl group on the tail, which reduces it's ability to get across the blood brain barrier, so you won't really catch a buzz taking it. Is is, however, a precursor to meth, which is why it's behind the counter and why every old biddy working the Wal-Mart pharmacy will stare daggers at you when you buy any.
